text: Had char siew noodles for $4.50. Good portions and char siew tasty. FYI the char siew are covered by the noodles after I tossed it. Sauce is on the sweeter side.

The Bbq pork not bad, requested for half fat half lean meat, gotten mostly fat. Though it's still nice but gets a little Jialek after 2 pieces. Guess next time I'll just stick to the regular cuts ðŸ˜œ.

Staff wearing chin mask. No glove. Chatting with char grill employee. Doesn't wash hands before food prep. Rubs his nose vigorously before proceeding to portion meat. I ask how much? Takes the ten dollars from my hand without answer.

Even the rojak auntie is infinitely more polite than this sorry excuse for a hawker. Either retrain him or replace him.

I order packet, apparently the only way to get chilli , you must ask for it.
